    "editor": "code",
    "content": "Druzar is a mid-sized city in the south of Alastria.\n\nRefugees from Etros fleeing the Etrousan Empire's advance have flocked to  the city in recent years. Some were let in after pleas from Archdeacon Warvyn Enbabenen of St. Rina's (Rina Riversong) Cathedral. In more recent times however, the city's residents have advocated for a more isolationist approach. Thus, non-Alastrian citizens have been relegated to the outskirts beyond the city walls. A slum filled with temporary structures now surrounds the cities, lawless and destitute. To protect traders and travellers passing through the city, the main road in and out is heavily policed by the city guard. Travellers will be accosted by street urchins and peddlers, but anyone too intrusive is quickly rebuked by the guards. The main road is kept clean and orderly, but even moving slightly into the slum backstreets reveals the truly desparate conditions the refugees live in.\n\n",
